============================================================
02 – TEAM PERFORMANCE ANALYSIS (04_02.csv)
============================================================

Description:
This section analyzes team-level performance using multiple
visualizations. The goal is to evaluate how teams perform
in terms of wins, scoring ability, efficiency, and overall
playing style.

The analysis combines ranking charts, scatter plots, and
heatmaps to provide both descriptive and relational insights.


------------------------------------------------------------
Diagrams & Analysis
------------------------------------------------------------


1. Top 10 Teams by Total Wins (teams_top_wins.png)

Description:
This chart ranks teams based on the total number of matches
won across all seasons.

Comment:
Top teams such as Manchester City, Manchester United, Chelsea,
and Liverpool dominate this ranking, reflecting long-term
consistency and success.


------------------------------------------------------------


2. Top 10 Teams by Win Rate (teams_win_rate.png)

Description:
Ranks teams based on their win percentage rather than total wins.

Comment:
Manchester City stands out with the highest win rate, indicating
not just participation but efficiency. This metric highlights
true performance quality.


------------------------------------------------------------


3. Top 10 Teams by Average Goals Scored (teams_avg_goals.png)

Description:
Shows the most offensively strong teams based on average goals.

Comment:
Manchester City leads clearly, followed by Liverpool and Arsenal,
indicating strong attacking capabilities among top teams.


------------------------------------------------------------


4. Top 10 Teams by Goal Difference (teams_goal_diff.png)

Description:
Displays the difference between goals scored and conceded.

Comment:
Teams with high goal difference (e.g. Manchester City) combine
strong offense with solid defense, making this one of the most
important performance indicators.


------------------------------------------------------------


5. Home vs Away Win Rate (home_vs_away_win_rate.png)

Description:
Compares team performance when playing at home vs away.

Comment:
Most teams perform significantly better at home, confirming the
existence of a strong home advantage in football. However, top
teams still maintain solid performance away from home.


------------------------------------------------------------


6. Attacking vs Defensive Profile (teams_attack_vs_defense_scatter.png)

Description:
Scatter plot showing average goals scored vs goals conceded.

Comment:
Top teams (e.g. Manchester City, Liverpool) are located in the
bottom-right area, meaning high scoring and low conceding.
Weaker teams tend to concede more and score less.


------------------------------------------------------------


7. Win Rate vs Goal Difference (winrate_vs_goaldiff.png)

Description:
Scatter plot analyzing the relationship between goal difference
and win rate.

Comment:
There is a strong positive relationship: teams with higher goal
difference tend to have higher win rates. This confirms that
goal difference is a key predictor of success.


------------------------------------------------------------


8. Correlation Heatmap of Team Metrics (team_correlation_heatmap.png)

Description:
Shows correlations between wins, win rate, goals scored,
goals conceded, and goal difference.

Comment:
Strong positive correlations exist between:
- win rate and goal difference
- wins and goals scored

Negative correlation is observed with goals conceded,
highlighting the importance of defensive performance.


------------------------------------------------------------


9. Home vs Away Correlation Heatmap (home_away_correlation.png)

Description:
Shows relationships between home and away performance metrics.

Comment:
Strong negative correlations between wins and losses confirm
expected behavior (more wins → fewer losses).
A strong positive relationship between home and away win rates
suggests that strong teams perform well in both conditions.


------------------------------------------------------------
Summary
------------------------------------------------------------

This section provides a comprehensive evaluation of team
performance by combining ranking, comparison, and correlation
analysis.

It highlights that successful teams:
- score more goals
- concede fewer goals
- maintain strong performance both home and away

These insights form the foundation for understanding team
behavior before moving into detailed matchup analysis.